The paper deals with consistency tuning in distributed datastores, which is a topic related to both database systems (cs.DB) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of machine learning algorithms such as decision tree learning suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), while the focus on predictive frameworks and optimization suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
